        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-07-14 20:30:56.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 11:\n\n> Patch Set 8: Code-Review+1\n> \n> On the REQ-321 topic (@Vijay).\n> We discussed this with TSC, and the situation is following:\n> 1. We have released the CertService in ONAP/Frankfurt, following all quality criteria.\n> 2. We are not really planning changes in CertService, other than bugFixes, if any would be found\n> 3. Following the changes in ONAP architecture (Istio intro, Keycloak, Ingress), CertService might be moved to the OOM project, as it would expand K8S native capabilities.\n> 4. We are totally committed to support the CertService project \n> (correct bugs, write release notes, update the documentation, self-release containers,...)... assuming we find some bugs during the integration with CertService Client.\n> \n> Due to the fact, that in this DCAE task, we actually integrate with an existing CertService Client container, rather than enhance the CertService Client, we removed the dependency to AAF project from REQ-321 and REQ-318.\n\nDamian - Okay, thanks for clarification.",
        "patchset_number": 11
      },
